WEBVTT

00:00:14.285 --> 00:00:15.453
From now on,

00:00:16.704 --> 00:00:18.331
can I do as I please?

00:00:27.632 --> 00:00:29.926
Well, I…

00:00:30.009 --> 00:00:32.762
What are you two doing over there?
Come in, Kyeong-nam!

00:00:35.807 --> 00:00:36.891
Let's go inside.

00:00:41.729 --> 00:00:43.982
How could you not remember what you drew?

00:00:44.065 --> 00:00:46.609
Episode 17, Si-woo and Na-ra's first kiss.

00:00:46.693 --> 00:00:49.571
Ms. Jang comes over and slaps her.
Don't you remember?

00:00:49.654 --> 00:00:52.407
Why do you have my work memorized?
That's creepy.

00:00:52.490 --> 00:00:54.576
I hate it so much that I can't look away.

00:00:54.659 --> 00:00:56.953
You're dissing my work, aren't you?

00:00:57.036 --> 00:00:58.204
You can't even draw.

00:00:58.288 --> 00:01:01.499
Being an author
is not only about drawing well.

00:01:01.583 --> 00:01:04.878
It's about diligence and originality.
Just memorize that.

00:01:04.961 --> 00:01:08.256
Hey, anyone can talk about diligence,
but not you.

00:01:08.339 --> 00:01:12.093
I heard that Park and Seo here
are working overtime every Friday.

00:01:14.012 --> 00:01:16.055
Aren't I the only author on Fridays?

00:01:16.139 --> 00:01:17.807
I always send in my work early.

00:01:18.683 --> 00:01:19.517
Yeah…

00:01:21.978 --> 00:01:23.062
The thing is…

00:01:23.146 --> 00:01:26.941
He must be working late all the time
because your files are a mess.

00:01:27.025 --> 00:01:28.067
No, they're not.

00:01:28.151 --> 00:01:30.612
I do have rather high standards, so…

00:01:30.695 --> 00:01:32.697
-Huh?
-That's why.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:37.243
I bet you want to work with someone
who can actually draw, right?

00:01:37.952 --> 00:01:39.913
But I think he draws well.

00:01:40.496 --> 00:01:41.664
What? Who draws well?

00:01:41.748 --> 00:01:45.835
That piece. Wasn't it done by you?

00:01:47.503 --> 00:01:50.089
What? Was that how you originally drew?

00:01:50.173 --> 00:01:52.300
That's not my work.

00:01:52.383 --> 00:01:55.929
Right? I knew it was so good.
Who's the artist?

00:01:57.096 --> 00:01:58.723
-This guy.
-Huh?

00:02:01.142 --> 00:02:03.436
He gave it to me
when I moved into this studio.

00:02:03.519 --> 00:02:05.396
Whoa, how are you so good?

00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:07.148
You guys didn't know?

00:02:07.732 --> 00:02:10.777
Kyeong-nam was my art instructor
when I was preparing for college.

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:11.694
Really?

00:02:11.778 --> 00:02:15.406
Well, it was just a part-time gig
when I was in college.

00:02:16.074 --> 00:02:18.034
You should do this for a living.

00:02:18.117 --> 00:02:19.244
Such a waste of talent.

00:02:19.327 --> 00:02:20.578
Right?

00:02:21.246 --> 00:02:23.665
See? Others see things the way I do.

00:02:23.748 --> 00:02:25.041
Stop.

00:02:25.124 --> 00:02:26.793
Plenty of people can draw like me.

00:02:26.876 --> 00:02:28.711
Come on. That's not true.

00:02:30.797 --> 00:02:32.298
Just worry about yourself.

00:02:32.382 --> 00:02:33.716
I'll handle it myself.

00:02:35.468 --> 00:02:37.470
This is the next episode.

00:02:38.012 --> 00:02:38.846
If I do this,

00:02:40.014 --> 00:02:41.683
don't you think it would be good?

00:02:41.766 --> 00:02:43.184
-It's nice.
-Right?

00:02:50.608 --> 00:02:52.777
Hwany, can I use your charger?

00:02:52.860 --> 00:02:55.446
There's one next to the sofa. Yes.

00:03:14.382 --> 00:03:15.591
Is he asleep?

00:03:16.467 --> 00:03:19.637
From now on, can I do as I please?

00:03:20.138 --> 00:03:22.223
What did he even mean by that?

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:35.361
Are you doing okay?

00:03:35.445 --> 00:03:38.281
What? What do you mean?

00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:39.824
That.

00:03:41.451 --> 00:03:42.452
"That"?

00:03:58.634 --> 00:03:59.469
This.

00:04:07.518 --> 00:04:08.936
It's gotten a lot better.

00:04:14.108 --> 00:04:15.276
I'm screwed.

00:04:21.824 --> 00:04:23.743
EPISODE 8
THE ODD OR EVEN GAME

00:04:34.962 --> 00:04:36.047
Are you doing okay?

00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:37.298
Damn it!

00:04:40.259 --> 00:04:41.135
I miss you.

00:04:44.305 --> 00:04:45.390
From now on,

00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:47.767
can I do as I please?

00:04:50.019 --> 00:04:51.562
Let's go!

00:05:05.159 --> 00:05:06.160
Hello?

00:05:06.244 --> 00:05:08.496
Hey, where are you?
I'm near your place right now.

00:05:08.579 --> 00:05:10.081
What are you doing here?

00:05:10.748 --> 00:05:13.084
I was feeling down, so I went for a run.

00:05:13.167 --> 00:05:14.085
In this weather?

00:05:14.168 --> 00:05:16.838
Can I come over?
I even bought some bungeo-ppang.

00:05:16.921 --> 00:05:19.882
You should have told me sooner!
I'm at the department store.

00:05:19.966 --> 00:05:20.800
Huh?

00:05:21.843 --> 00:05:22.927
You're shopping again?

00:05:23.010 --> 00:05:26.347
No, my vacuum cleaner broke down,
so I have to buy a new one.

00:05:26.848 --> 00:05:29.100
Hey, that's still shopping.

00:05:29.183 --> 00:05:30.017
Is it?

00:05:30.101 --> 00:05:33.271
A lot of newlyweds frequent our store,
so the package discounts…

00:05:33.354 --> 00:05:34.605
Holy!

00:05:34.689 --> 00:05:36.149
…explained in detail.

00:05:36.232 --> 00:05:38.109
-Physical stores are our strength.
-Hello?

00:05:38.192 --> 00:05:40.236
-What is it?
-God, that scared me.

00:05:40.945 --> 00:05:42.530
It's the guy from my blind date.

00:05:43.197 --> 00:05:44.699
He works here. I remember now.

00:05:45.616 --> 00:05:49.287
What do I do?
I really need to buy a vacuum cleaner.

00:05:49.370 --> 00:05:51.664
Hey, that's great. Ask him for a discount.

00:05:51.747 --> 00:05:54.208
Are you insane?
I ghosted him after that day.

00:05:54.876 --> 00:05:56.502
Whatever! I'll call you back.

00:05:57.295 --> 00:06:00.214
So be prepared for that,
and the high-discount items…

00:06:00.298 --> 00:06:02.884
I'm running out of places to go
because of all the dates.

00:06:03.801 --> 00:06:05.303
Talk about karma.

00:06:07.013 --> 00:06:09.891
This is a place where any romance
you desire becomes reality.

00:06:10.808 --> 00:06:13.019
There are 900 themes just for you.

00:06:14.020 --> 00:06:17.398
So, who will you be dating today?

00:06:40.713 --> 00:06:41.547
Hello.

00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:43.674
-Doors opening.
-Hi.

00:06:53.726 --> 00:06:54.936
Doors closing.

00:07:16.332 --> 00:07:17.833
So I can get on with you.

00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:43.734
Hi.

00:07:43.818 --> 00:07:44.902
Hey, what's up?

00:08:05.590 --> 00:08:07.675
Come on, focus.

00:08:17.893 --> 00:08:18.728
What is it?

00:08:21.606 --> 00:08:23.608
Did you come here looking for me?

00:08:51.344 --> 00:08:52.970
I came here for this.

00:08:56.140 --> 00:08:57.475
I see. Right!

00:08:58.142 --> 00:08:59.644
You can take it.

00:09:00.186 --> 00:09:01.020
Okay.

00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:07.193
Drink this while you work.

00:09:08.944 --> 00:09:10.237
You got that for me?

00:09:10.821 --> 00:09:12.782
Yes. I had to come anyway, so…

00:09:15.451 --> 00:09:17.870
Come to think of it,
they are gone already.

00:09:19.538 --> 00:09:20.623
What do you mean?

00:09:21.957 --> 00:09:22.792
Your bangs.

00:09:24.710 --> 00:09:25.711
Looked good on you.

00:09:30.174 --> 00:09:31.008
Bye now.

00:09:31.884 --> 00:09:32.802
Okay.

00:10:03.499 --> 00:10:04.917
Stop being conscious of him.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:07.253
Don't show that you're losing composure!

00:10:07.336 --> 00:10:08.713
Get a grip!

00:10:25.354 --> 00:10:26.439
Ms. Seo.

00:10:29.567 --> 00:10:31.861
Here. This is yours.

00:10:33.070 --> 00:10:33.946
This is…

00:10:34.029 --> 00:10:35.573
I picked it up here in the lobby.

00:10:37.241 --> 00:10:40.161
I thought I had lost it. Thank you.

00:10:41.078 --> 00:10:42.079
That was

00:10:42.830 --> 00:10:44.039
my gift, by the way.

00:10:45.583 --> 00:10:48.753
I'm the one who put it in there
for the gift draw.

00:10:50.880 --> 00:10:53.632
You are the one who bought this? This?

00:10:54.425 --> 00:10:57.928
Yes. I bought this one for no reason
and put it in the box.

00:11:00.806 --> 00:11:03.392
-I didn't know that.
-Naturally. It was an anonymous draw.

00:11:06.312 --> 00:11:08.230
Anyway, thank you.

00:11:08.814 --> 00:11:10.483
Sure. See you tomorrow.

00:11:15.029 --> 00:11:16.030
Ms. Seo?

00:11:18.032 --> 00:11:20.367
Will you be putting it on again?

00:11:25.039 --> 00:11:26.207
Do whatever you'd like.

00:11:46.602 --> 00:11:47.853
This is driving me crazy.

00:11:52.733 --> 00:11:53.859
Good night.

00:11:55.736 --> 00:11:56.570
What was that?

00:12:05.079 --> 00:12:06.247
PRODUCER PARK
GOOD NIGHT

00:12:07.748 --> 00:12:10.918
Wait, did he just send me
a private message?

00:12:11.502 --> 00:12:12.962
This is crazy.

00:12:13.546 --> 00:12:14.380
Good night.

00:12:15.589 --> 00:12:18.968
Good night.

00:12:22.555 --> 00:12:24.306
This really is crazy.

00:12:32.398 --> 00:12:33.232
Huh?

00:12:34.149 --> 00:12:36.151
Why do I look so tired?

00:12:46.745 --> 00:12:47.997
None of this is working.

00:12:48.622 --> 00:12:50.833
Come to think of it,
they are gone already.

00:12:50.916 --> 00:12:51.917
Your bangs.

00:12:53.127 --> 00:12:54.378
Looked good on you.

00:13:15.107 --> 00:13:15.941
Gotcha.

00:13:27.536 --> 00:13:28.662
What?

00:13:28.746 --> 00:13:32.124
You have makeup on,
so why are you wearing a cap?

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:33.834
What?

00:13:35.753 --> 00:13:37.421
I don't know. I just put it on.

00:13:40.633 --> 00:13:41.634
You worked all night?

00:13:42.217 --> 00:13:44.720
So you can reclaim the top spot for TMTK?

00:13:44.803 --> 00:13:46.388
Don't push yourself too hard.

00:13:46.472 --> 00:13:49.141
Ms. Seo, you look really exhausted.

00:13:49.224 --> 00:13:50.059
Yeah.

00:13:51.477 --> 00:13:52.478
I do?

00:13:52.561 --> 00:13:55.064
-Let's eat something nice today, okay?
-Love it.

00:13:55.147 --> 00:13:57.608
The platform and genre
will remain the same.

00:13:57.691 --> 00:14:00.694
Even for them, making a game
out of a series that's just started…

00:14:00.778 --> 00:14:02.947
I guess Kyeong-nam really is taking off.

00:14:03.030 --> 00:14:08.035
As if dethroning TMTK wasn't enough,
they're planning a game based on PlanC.

00:14:10.079 --> 00:14:12.373
A game? What kind of game?

00:14:12.873 --> 00:14:16.043
It seems he's in serious talks
with DU right now.

00:14:16.126 --> 00:14:19.463
What is it with everything
Park Kyeong-nam touches?

00:14:19.546 --> 00:14:22.967
At this rate, he's going to turn Hwany
into the undisputed champion.

00:14:23.050 --> 00:14:25.719
Look at Mr. Hwang
grinning from ear to ear.

00:14:25.803 --> 00:14:28.389
You know, Kyeong-nam scares me
more than anyone else.

00:14:28.472 --> 00:14:30.557
Such a solid guy, isn't he?

00:14:35.437 --> 00:14:36.355
Hey.

00:14:38.399 --> 00:14:39.233
Hello?

00:14:40.943 --> 00:14:42.277
Hello!

00:14:42.778 --> 00:14:43.612
Oh, yes?

00:14:43.696 --> 00:14:45.364
You are not listening to me.

00:14:45.447 --> 00:14:47.616
Why are you zoning out like that?

00:14:48.158 --> 00:14:49.368
Sorry. What did you say?

00:14:50.202 --> 00:14:53.455
I got a hand X-ray taken.

00:14:53.539 --> 00:14:57.292
The inflammation's so bad
that I have to eat with my left hand.

00:14:57.376 --> 00:14:59.378
But I can't use chopsticks with it, can I?

00:14:59.461 --> 00:15:00.546
Right.

00:15:01.755 --> 00:15:03.924
So stop ordering noodles for lunch.

00:15:06.260 --> 00:15:07.761
Okay. Understood.

00:15:19.231 --> 00:15:23.318
As if dethroning TMTK wasn't enough,
they're planning a game based on PlanC.

00:15:23.402 --> 00:15:26.822
At this rate, he's going to turn Hwany
into the undisputed champion.

00:15:27.781 --> 00:15:28.782
Ms. Yun!

00:15:29.658 --> 00:15:32.119
Don't you realize
how bad things are right now?

00:15:32.202 --> 00:15:34.329
We really need our heads in the game.

00:15:34.413 --> 00:15:36.832
The gap between PlanC and us
keeps widening.

00:15:36.915 --> 00:15:38.584
It's great that you're dating,

00:15:38.667 --> 00:15:41.587
but are you just going to give up on TMTK?

00:15:42.588 --> 00:15:44.798
Why are you being so serious
all of a sudden?

00:15:45.299 --> 00:15:46.925
All I did was text my boyfriend.

00:15:47.009 --> 00:15:48.343
How would men

00:15:48.427 --> 00:15:50.804
make any meaningful contribution
to our lives?

00:15:51.638 --> 00:15:53.098
-Huh?
-Think about it!

00:15:53.182 --> 00:15:56.060
Is it okay to let our relationships
affect our livelihoods?

00:15:56.143 --> 00:15:58.479
No, Ms. Yun. It's not okay.

00:15:59.396 --> 00:16:00.981
Where is this coming from?

00:16:02.066 --> 00:16:05.402
-Can't you just let me handle it myself?
-Absolutely not.

00:16:18.373 --> 00:16:19.875
You take the subway, right?

00:16:20.709 --> 00:16:23.670
I was thinking of taking the subway too.
We can go together.

00:16:39.144 --> 00:16:40.562
By the way,

00:16:40.646 --> 00:16:43.107
did you wear a cap
so you wouldn't look pretty for me?

00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:44.066
What?

00:16:45.275 --> 00:16:48.612
Oh, this? Nope, not at all.

00:16:49.863 --> 00:16:50.739
I thought maybe.

00:16:54.868 --> 00:16:58.122
Oh, I just remembered.
I have to take the bus today.

00:16:58.205 --> 00:16:59.832
Huh? You're taking the bus now?

00:16:59.915 --> 00:17:01.667
Yes. Have a safe trip home.

00:17:01.750 --> 00:17:02.626
Wait!

00:17:16.932 --> 00:17:18.308
But that bus is…

00:17:19.685 --> 00:17:22.646
Fasten your seatbelts.
We're approaching the highway.

00:17:23.313 --> 00:17:24.398
The highway?

00:17:25.315 --> 00:17:28.777
Wait, excuse me.
Where is this bus headed right now?

00:17:28.861 --> 00:17:29.695
Incheon.

00:17:30.279 --> 00:17:31.697
Incheon?

00:17:33.407 --> 00:17:35.826
You should sit back down. It's dangerous!

00:17:37.744 --> 00:17:39.329
He could have told me.

00:17:49.131 --> 00:17:50.549
The one who set us up told me

00:17:50.632 --> 00:17:54.344
that this will be your last blind date,
regardless of how it turns out.

00:17:55.637 --> 00:17:56.471
That's right.

00:17:56.555 --> 00:17:57.890
May I ask why?

00:18:00.559 --> 00:18:03.061
I've just grown really tired.

00:18:05.480 --> 00:18:06.398
I feel the same way.

00:18:06.481 --> 00:18:09.651
It's really hard to find someone you like.

00:18:09.735 --> 00:18:10.777
I agree.

00:18:10.861 --> 00:18:12.070
Do you have a type?

00:18:14.615 --> 00:18:15.949
I like

00:18:17.117 --> 00:18:19.369
men who are full of contradictions.

00:18:19.453 --> 00:18:22.581
-Full of contradictions?
-Yes.

00:18:23.415 --> 00:18:25.375
Someone who's neat but sexy,

00:18:25.459 --> 00:18:26.627
gentle but bad,

00:18:26.710 --> 00:18:28.212
and smart but sloppy.

00:18:28.295 --> 00:18:30.964
He should have a steady job
but be a free spirit,

00:18:31.048 --> 00:18:33.884
love books
without looking like a bookworm,

00:18:33.967 --> 00:18:37.012
have hard muscles but a soft heart,
and finally,

00:18:37.095 --> 00:18:39.806
be the kind of man
who says he'd never fall for me

00:18:39.890 --> 00:18:42.017
but loves me more than anyone else.

00:18:44.770 --> 00:18:46.188
-I see.
-Should I keep going?

00:18:47.564 --> 00:18:50.150
Excuse me. I need to take this call.

00:19:20.472 --> 00:19:21.306
Huh?

00:19:21.390 --> 00:19:22.766
The first song goes to

00:19:23.433 --> 00:19:27.604
the lady who asks for too much
but is beautiful enough to be forgiven.

00:19:29.106 --> 00:19:31.024
Is it over between you and that man?

00:19:33.068 --> 00:19:35.404
Well, yes, I suppose…

00:19:35.487 --> 00:19:37.072
I want you to forget about him.

00:19:48.375 --> 00:19:51.795
A story just for two of us

00:19:51.878 --> 00:19:55.716
The moon is shining on us

00:19:56.216 --> 00:20:00.178
My destiny, I'll hold you tight

00:20:02.431 --> 00:20:04.599
You're the one

00:20:04.683 --> 00:20:08.520
I sing this song for you

00:20:08.603 --> 00:20:12.941
I love you, I love you

00:20:13.025 --> 00:20:16.987
Now I confess my whole heart

00:20:17.654 --> 00:20:19.948
To you

00:20:23.660 --> 00:20:27.664
Congratulations, Ms. Lee Ji-yeon,
on meeting your first date!

00:20:46.391 --> 00:20:47.392
Awesome.

00:20:55.984 --> 00:21:00.530
The tree sure is bare this year,
with how busy Director Hwang is.

00:21:01.031 --> 00:21:05.118
I know. He used to gather us up
and decorate it, like it was a tradition.

00:21:05.202 --> 00:21:06.370
It's kind of sad.

00:21:07.371 --> 00:21:08.372
What do you mean?

00:21:10.207 --> 00:21:13.710
You know, a Christmas tree
is supposed to be all shiny and stuff.

00:21:15.045 --> 00:21:18.548
So the holidays have a way of making
even Seo Mi-rae sentimental.

00:21:19.049 --> 00:21:20.717
What are you all doing tomorrow?

00:21:20.801 --> 00:21:23.762
I'll probably watch dramas at home.

00:21:23.845 --> 00:21:26.932
I'm going on a staycation with friends.
What about you?

00:21:27.015 --> 00:21:29.684
-I'm going to church with my mom.
-I have it better.

00:21:30.352 --> 00:21:32.437
How about we go for a drink after work?

00:21:33.146 --> 00:21:35.565
Oh, the bars might be packed
since it's Christmas Eve.

00:21:35.649 --> 00:21:37.317
-I can't go.
-Why not?

00:21:37.401 --> 00:21:40.320
Christmas Eve or not,
today's just a TMTK update day for me.

00:21:42.656 --> 00:21:44.032
Oh well, let's go without her.

00:21:45.158 --> 00:21:46.034
Kyeong-nam.

00:21:47.369 --> 00:21:48.870
Are you also working late today?

00:21:49.579 --> 00:21:50.414
Yes.

00:21:51.998 --> 00:21:53.166
You poor things.

00:21:53.667 --> 00:21:58.255
Tell Hwany to take it easy.
He should pace himself while he's young.

00:22:02.843 --> 00:22:05.470
So, what about that place
we went to last time?

00:22:14.646 --> 00:22:18.400
Aren't I the only author on Fridays?
I always send in my work early.

00:22:20.193 --> 00:22:21.027
The thing is…

00:22:31.580 --> 00:22:33.039
Mr. Park.

00:22:35.208 --> 00:22:38.879
I guess Hwany is also late
with his submission today.

00:22:39.463 --> 00:22:40.297
No.

00:22:41.131 --> 00:22:41.965
Sorry?

00:22:42.674 --> 00:22:43.675
He already sent it.

00:22:47.429 --> 00:22:49.181
Then why are you still…

00:22:50.891 --> 00:22:52.434
Because I want to be here.

00:23:02.110 --> 00:23:04.696
Oh, I see. All right!

00:23:18.919 --> 00:23:19.753
YUN SONG

00:23:24.466 --> 00:23:25.300
UPLOAD COMPLETE

00:23:35.727 --> 00:23:36.561
What?

00:23:41.233 --> 00:23:42.067
What's going on?

00:23:43.360 --> 00:23:44.778
Is it a blackout?

00:24:29.906 --> 00:24:31.741
You said it made you sad, so…

00:24:36.329 --> 00:24:37.664
It's kind of sad.

00:24:38.873 --> 00:24:39.958
What do you mean?

00:24:40.041 --> 00:24:44.838
You know, a Christmas tree
is supposed to be all shiny and stuff.

00:25:21.374 --> 00:25:22.208
Ms. Seo.

00:25:25.420 --> 00:25:26.880
Are you taking the bus again?

00:25:29.549 --> 00:25:30.634
No.

00:25:40.644 --> 00:25:41.478
Thank you.

00:25:42.437 --> 00:25:45.690
I felt the Christmas spirit thanks to you.
It was nice.

00:25:47.067 --> 00:25:47.942
I enjoyed it.

00:25:55.659 --> 00:25:59.579
I heard about the PlanC game coming out.
Congratulations.

00:26:00.163 --> 00:26:02.082
It hasn't even been confirmed yet.

00:26:04.626 --> 00:26:07.087
How are you so good at everything you do?

00:26:08.254 --> 00:26:11.341
I get the impression that
you wouldn't have much to worry about.

00:26:11.883 --> 00:26:13.301
You do everything so easily.

00:26:14.386 --> 00:26:15.720
Did I come across that way?

00:26:16.221 --> 00:26:17.305
I'm not like that.

00:26:25.438 --> 00:26:26.940
LEE KYU-TAE SOLO EXHIBITION

00:26:27.023 --> 00:26:28.858
Do you know this artist?

00:26:30.193 --> 00:26:32.779
I buy their illustrated calendars
every year.

00:26:33.446 --> 00:26:37.200
Come to think of it, I get similar vibes
from their pieces as yours.

00:26:37.701 --> 00:26:39.953
I used to like this artist too.

00:26:41.579 --> 00:26:42.580
I see.

00:26:43.707 --> 00:26:45.625
The exhibition is going to end soon.

00:26:46.418 --> 00:26:47.252
It seems so.

00:26:50.630 --> 00:26:51.548
Wanna go with me?

00:26:56.636 --> 00:26:58.263
Did that come off too casually?

00:26:59.639 --> 00:27:01.558
Take your time and let me know.

00:27:12.444 --> 00:27:13.611
Aren't you hungry?

00:27:15.989 --> 00:27:17.991
It seemed like you were skipping dinner.

00:27:33.006 --> 00:27:37.093
By the way, why did you stop drawing?
You seemed to have a lot of talent.

00:27:39.387 --> 00:27:40.722
I didn't feel it anymore.

00:27:42.056 --> 00:27:42.891
Huh?

00:27:44.350 --> 00:27:46.770
Drawing used to mean everything to me,

00:27:47.270 --> 00:27:49.272
but suddenly it just felt different.

00:27:50.440 --> 00:27:52.108
I felt bad about changing,

00:27:52.609 --> 00:27:55.987
but at the same time, I was excited
to find something else I liked as much.

00:27:56.613 --> 00:27:57.447
That's why I quit.

00:28:00.700 --> 00:28:02.869
So did you find something
you liked as much?

00:28:03.453 --> 00:28:04.662
Turns out it wasn't easy

00:28:05.246 --> 00:28:08.833
to like something that much,
that consistently.

00:28:15.048 --> 00:28:16.716
-See you, then.
-Bye.

00:28:17.967 --> 00:28:19.260
Oh, wait.

00:28:33.149 --> 00:28:34.567
Read it later.

00:28:35.860 --> 00:28:36.694
Okay.

00:28:37.529 --> 00:28:38.363
Bye.

00:29:08.017 --> 00:29:10.770
Let's eat together next time.
Just the two of us.

00:29:19.696 --> 00:29:22.282
I wanted to tell you that I like you.

00:29:33.877 --> 00:29:35.295
Did you get home okay?

00:29:40.425 --> 00:29:41.676
YES

00:29:42.343 --> 00:29:43.177
GU YEONG-IL

00:29:43.261 --> 00:29:45.054
How much longer should I wait?

00:29:50.768 --> 00:29:52.770
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

00:29:53.897 --> 00:29:56.733
How did I end up like this?

00:30:04.115 --> 00:30:04.949
You're here.

00:30:15.460 --> 00:30:17.378
-Hey--
-I got a bite.

00:30:25.553 --> 00:30:28.723
It seems they are only biting
whenever I try to say something.

00:30:29.933 --> 00:30:30.850
Seems so.

00:30:31.684 --> 00:30:32.518
How odd.

00:30:38.066 --> 00:30:38.900
What's wrong?

00:30:48.701 --> 00:30:50.536
I confessed my feelings to you,

00:30:50.620 --> 00:30:53.790
and now you're talking to me seriously
with a serious look.

00:30:53.873 --> 00:30:54.832
I'm scared.

00:30:58.503 --> 00:30:59.629
That I might say no?

00:31:01.089 --> 00:31:02.340
Are you going to?

00:31:15.561 --> 00:31:17.063
I can't catch a thing today.

00:31:19.315 --> 00:31:20.149
Let's go.

00:31:39.043 --> 00:31:40.044
Want me to draw you?

00:31:53.474 --> 00:31:54.475
Just act natural.

00:31:56.436 --> 00:31:57.270
Okay.

00:32:08.322 --> 00:32:09.157
Ms. Seo.

00:32:13.244 --> 00:32:14.579
I like you.

00:32:17.290 --> 00:32:18.458
From now on…

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:21.586
can I do as I please?

00:32:33.473 --> 00:32:34.474
What's wrong?

00:32:41.147 --> 00:32:41.981
I'm sorry.

00:32:43.357 --> 00:32:44.442
What?

00:32:44.525 --> 00:32:45.443
Well,

00:32:46.444 --> 00:32:48.112
I won't be coming back here anymore.

00:32:51.866 --> 00:32:52.700
Why is that?

00:32:53.409 --> 00:32:55.787
You wouldn't understand
even if I told you,

00:32:56.579 --> 00:33:00.416
but the more I meet you,
the more I keep falling for someone.

00:33:01.751 --> 00:33:02.960
And that feels

00:33:04.003 --> 00:33:06.172
as though that person is having it easy.

00:33:08.841 --> 00:33:11.844
Do you mean that,
even when you're with me,

00:33:12.512 --> 00:33:14.847
another man keeps coming to mind?

00:33:20.853 --> 00:33:21.854
Do you like him?

00:33:28.027 --> 00:33:29.112
I don't know.

00:33:33.574 --> 00:33:35.660
How do you not know your own feelings?

00:33:35.743 --> 00:33:37.120
It's frustrating for me too.

00:33:37.745 --> 00:33:40.915
How about you?
Do you know what it is to like someone?

00:33:40.998 --> 00:33:43.334
You don't know what it's like
to truly like someone.

00:33:43.417 --> 00:33:44.627
I know.

00:33:46.420 --> 00:33:50.591
It's knowing you won't change,
even if the person you're with does.

00:33:53.094 --> 00:33:54.512
I never changed.

00:33:55.012 --> 00:33:56.347
Mi-rae.

00:33:56.430 --> 00:33:58.266
We all change.

00:33:58.850 --> 00:34:00.309
You've also changed.

00:34:06.107 --> 00:34:08.109
What you said about your drawings…

00:34:09.402 --> 00:34:12.238
Why are you so obsessed
with what changes and what doesn't?

00:34:13.364 --> 00:34:16.367
Is it such a big deal?
Why are you so obsessed with it?

00:34:17.493 --> 00:34:19.996
Could there be any other reason?

00:34:22.582 --> 00:34:24.667
That's the way I am. I can't help it.

00:34:27.044 --> 00:34:28.129
The way you are?

00:34:30.506 --> 00:34:32.508
There is a reason for everything.

00:34:33.801 --> 00:34:34.969
Because it was me

00:34:36.262 --> 00:34:37.513
who made you.

00:34:39.974 --> 00:34:41.100
Ms. Seo Mi-rae.

00:34:41.976 --> 00:34:43.936
I'm sure you know what I want…

00:34:44.520 --> 00:34:46.397
Even if you don't like me anymore…

00:34:47.064 --> 00:34:48.816
…and what I fear…

00:34:48.900 --> 00:34:50.568
…I won't ever change.

00:34:51.194 --> 00:34:53.029
…as well as I do.

00:34:53.112 --> 00:34:55.531
Because that's my way of liking someone.

00:34:56.157 --> 00:34:59.452
No. Perhaps even better than I do.

00:35:00.286 --> 00:35:01.370
Did he tell you

00:35:02.121 --> 00:35:03.122
that he won't change?

00:35:11.297 --> 00:35:12.632
I didn't feel it anymore.

00:35:12.715 --> 00:35:14.342
Turns out it wasn't easy

00:35:14.425 --> 00:35:18.221
to like something that much,
that consistently.

00:35:28.981 --> 00:35:30.733
When his feelings for you change,

00:35:31.776 --> 00:35:33.361
are you certain you won't get hurt?

00:35:41.035 --> 00:35:42.203
As for me…

00:35:44.538 --> 00:35:46.540
I won't ever hurt you.

00:35:48.709 --> 00:35:49.543
So,

00:35:51.420 --> 00:35:52.505
don't go.

00:36:14.110 --> 00:36:15.194
Ms. Seo.

00:36:22.118 --> 00:36:24.328
-It's the final evaluations already.
-So it is.

00:36:24.412 --> 00:36:27.290
Fantasy was super competitive this year.
How about you guys?

00:36:27.373 --> 00:36:29.583
Ours was intense as well.

00:36:29.667 --> 00:36:33.004
Kyeong-nam and Mi-rae would keep going
back and forth about who was right.

00:36:33.087 --> 00:36:33.921
All right.

00:36:34.005 --> 00:36:36.966
Mr. Hwang can't make it today,
so let's get started.

00:36:37.049 --> 00:36:37.883
-Okay.
-Sure.

00:36:42.513 --> 00:36:46.350
This one's well-balanced,
but isn't it a bit too old-fashioned?

00:36:46.434 --> 00:36:49.979
A bit lacking in that regard,
but at least it's a safe choice.

00:36:51.522 --> 00:36:57.361
It's not bad, but it's not great.
It's smooth, but it lacks an edge.

00:36:59.322 --> 00:37:00.906
Put it on hold for now?

00:37:02.158 --> 00:37:03.075
Okay.

00:37:03.159 --> 00:37:05.036
Who needs to use the restroom?

00:37:05.119 --> 00:37:06.829
-I do.
-Me too.

00:37:22.178 --> 00:37:24.930
I think every piece needs to pack a punch.

00:37:25.014 --> 00:37:26.265
The references…

00:37:26.349 --> 00:37:28.601
Oh, I left my phone behind.

00:37:28.684 --> 00:37:29.769
Make me a coffee.

00:37:34.273 --> 00:37:36.108
Go ahead. I'm not going to use it.

00:37:36.192 --> 00:37:37.193
Ms. Seo.

00:37:40.571 --> 00:37:41.489
Are you sick?

00:37:44.575 --> 00:37:45.618
No.

00:37:47.161 --> 00:37:49.163
You just don't look too good.

00:37:53.834 --> 00:37:55.169
Anyway, so…

00:37:58.214 --> 00:38:03.177
What you said about doing as you please,

00:38:03.677 --> 00:38:06.055
I get what you meant by that now.

00:38:06.972 --> 00:38:09.225
But whatever it is,

00:38:10.059 --> 00:38:13.145
I'd appreciate it
if you could stop doing it at work.

00:38:16.690 --> 00:38:18.609
At work?

00:38:23.030 --> 00:38:24.615
I didn't phrase that correctly.

00:38:26.158 --> 00:38:29.495
Just stop doing it altogether,
wherever it may be.

00:38:31.622 --> 00:38:33.040
Please.

00:38:40.339 --> 00:38:43.175
Huh? I said I wanted some coffee.

00:38:46.971 --> 00:38:47.972
You want one, yeah?

00:38:57.356 --> 00:38:59.024
-Move on to the next piece?
-Okay.

00:38:59.608 --> 00:39:02.153
A-606. Crimson-Eyed Elena.

00:39:02.736 --> 00:39:06.323
What do we have here?
I love the style. Who picked this one?

00:39:08.409 --> 00:39:11.829
Actually, we had mixed opinions
about this piece.

00:39:12.413 --> 00:39:13.247
So…

00:39:18.502 --> 00:39:19.920
I'm the one who approved of it.

00:39:20.421 --> 00:39:25.676
Kyeong-nam and Mi-rae
never saw eye to eye on this one.

00:39:28.846 --> 00:39:32.099
I think this piece is fully qualified.

00:39:32.766 --> 00:39:34.768
And Mi-rae? Are you still against it?

00:39:36.979 --> 00:39:37.813
Yes.

00:39:38.731 --> 00:39:39.565
I don't like it.

00:39:41.692 --> 00:39:43.569
It is a little rough around the edges.

00:39:44.778 --> 00:39:46.697
-What don't you like exactly?
-Huh?

00:39:50.868 --> 00:39:53.120
I think I've already told you
several times.

00:39:53.204 --> 00:39:55.456
This is a contest for rookies.

00:39:55.539 --> 00:39:59.960
Director Hwang told us to focus
on the potential, and I saw the potential.

00:40:01.295 --> 00:40:02.880
Well, I didn't see it.

00:40:02.963 --> 00:40:04.965
You almost changed your mind at one point.

00:40:09.178 --> 00:40:10.930
From start to finish, did you really

00:40:12.389 --> 00:40:13.724
hate all of it?

00:40:17.186 --> 00:40:18.020
Yes.

00:40:21.357 --> 00:40:23.025
And I don't think…

00:40:25.903 --> 00:40:27.321
that will ever change.

00:40:35.746 --> 00:40:37.998
Yes! Now that's what I call a meeting!

00:40:38.499 --> 00:40:42.419
Why don't we call it for today
and finish talking about it tomorrow?

00:40:42.503 --> 00:40:44.630
-Sounds good.
-Good work, everyone.

00:40:44.713 --> 00:40:46.215
We worked too hard today, huh?

00:40:46.715 --> 00:40:47.800
-Good work.
-I'm tired.

00:40:47.883 --> 00:40:48.884
Let's go.

00:40:51.470 --> 00:40:53.597
Good work, everyone.

00:41:42.521 --> 00:41:44.273
I just remembered

00:41:45.274 --> 00:41:49.153
why I was so adamant
about not dating anyone.

00:41:50.529 --> 00:41:51.697
But

00:41:52.323 --> 00:41:56.660
seeing how scared I am
of Kyeong-nam changing…

00:42:03.667 --> 00:42:07.546
I guess he really was the person
I truly liked.

00:42:09.798 --> 00:42:14.511
I used to think that you were the reason
Kyeong-nam made my heart race,

00:42:15.554 --> 00:42:17.139
but I think I must have…

00:42:20.517 --> 00:42:21.852
actually liked him.

00:42:24.313 --> 00:42:25.981
That's why I held onto you.

00:42:28.776 --> 00:42:30.319
I didn't wanna see you suffer.

00:42:31.737 --> 00:42:33.280
It's bound to end someday,

00:42:34.698 --> 00:42:36.700
and you will have to deal with it alone.

00:42:37.201 --> 00:42:39.036
Ending up alone again,

00:42:40.329 --> 00:42:41.747
you hate it more than anything.

00:42:43.332 --> 00:42:44.917
I wanted to forget.

00:42:45.000 --> 00:42:46.377
Are you okay?

00:42:52.257 --> 00:42:55.511
Goodness, you fool.

00:42:59.264 --> 00:43:02.643
MI-RAE, SE-JUNE

00:43:39.138 --> 00:43:40.973
Here's the shrimp ball.

00:43:42.516 --> 00:43:44.768
-You're not gonna let me have that?
-No way.

00:43:44.852 --> 00:43:47.020
-You're the best.
-Thank you, ma'am.

00:43:47.855 --> 00:43:49.189
-Here.
-Okay.

00:43:49.273 --> 00:43:50.941
Your legs are very tight, ma'am.

00:43:51.024 --> 00:43:52.526
Your hair's so damaged, ma'am.

00:43:52.609 --> 00:43:54.111
Easy. Do it from a distance.

00:43:54.194 --> 00:43:55.279
Right. I'm sorry.

00:43:55.362 --> 00:43:56.196
Look.

00:43:57.239 --> 00:43:58.741
It's hilarious. Look.

00:44:02.578 --> 00:44:05.998
What had always been part of a pair
was suddenly alone.

00:44:07.499 --> 00:44:10.753
When it dawned upon me
that he was never coming back,

00:44:11.670 --> 00:44:13.422
it hurt so much.

00:44:18.677 --> 00:44:20.012
And you're afraid

00:44:20.637 --> 00:44:22.306
that it might happen.

00:44:27.603 --> 00:44:29.354
The man I created…

00:44:31.440 --> 00:44:34.610
keeps weakening my resolve,
over and over again.

00:44:38.864 --> 00:44:39.948
You did well.

00:44:41.074 --> 00:44:42.242
It's the right thing.

00:45:00.385 --> 00:45:02.888
I buy their illustrated calendars
every year.

00:45:03.889 --> 00:45:05.140
Wanna go with me?

00:45:30.958 --> 00:45:35.128
If it's going to end anyway,
it's better not to start it at all.

00:45:49.935 --> 00:45:52.312
Jeong-hyu wrapped up this episode nicely.

00:45:52.396 --> 00:45:54.356
When should I pay off the setups?

00:45:57.526 --> 00:45:59.236
Hold on. I need to take this call.

00:46:00.445 --> 00:46:01.405
Hey, Mom.

00:46:12.791 --> 00:46:15.460
I'm sorry, but I guess…

00:46:15.544 --> 00:46:19.214
Three cups of coffee, three treats.
What are you getting at here?

00:46:19.715 --> 00:46:21.800
Well, since there are three of us--

00:46:21.884 --> 00:46:23.969
Again with the three!

00:46:24.052 --> 00:46:26.680
Are you putting it out there
that TMTK is in third place?

00:46:26.763 --> 00:46:28.390
…I'm not brave enough.

00:47:05.427 --> 00:47:07.763
Anyway, you all worked so hard last year.

00:47:07.846 --> 00:47:10.265
-Here's to us!
-Great work, everyone!

00:47:10.933 --> 00:47:13.268
It's time for me to share some good news.

00:47:13.352 --> 00:47:16.980
Oh well, I guess for you guys,
it might come across as somewhat sad news.

00:47:17.064 --> 00:47:19.358
Starting this year,

00:47:19.441 --> 00:47:23.320
we have decided to really jump into
the American webtoon platform race.

00:47:23.403 --> 00:47:27.074
And that's why we are going to send
Korea's finest over there.

00:47:27.991 --> 00:47:28.825
Who might that be?

00:47:33.622 --> 00:47:34.456
It's me.

00:47:37.918 --> 00:47:40.170
I'm leaving. For the States. As the CEO.

00:47:41.463 --> 00:47:44.007
Director Hwang! No, CEO Hwang!

00:47:44.091 --> 00:47:45.509
-Oh please!
-Congratulations!

00:47:45.592 --> 00:47:50.097
Come on, how are we supposed to manage
if you just leave us like that?

00:47:50.180 --> 00:47:53.976
Hey now, I still have a few months left.
Don't be like that.

00:47:54.059 --> 00:47:58.188
I'm a bit torn up
about having to leave you guys behind.

00:47:58.271 --> 00:48:00.524
We should start preparing
a farewell party, right?

00:48:00.607 --> 00:48:03.944
Of course.
A grand celebration that befits him.

00:48:04.027 --> 00:48:04.861
True.

00:48:04.945 --> 00:48:07.364
Hey! That was on me!

00:48:07.447 --> 00:48:09.032
-Thanks!
-I told you I was buying.

00:48:09.116 --> 00:48:10.534
-You're the best!
-Thank you.

00:48:10.617 --> 00:48:12.369
I'm spending it all before I leave!

00:48:12.452 --> 00:48:14.204
-Let's join him today.
-Director Hwang!

00:48:15.580 --> 00:48:16.748
-Where to?
-Let's go!

00:48:16.832 --> 00:48:20.002
-Awesome!
-Where is she going? Hey!

00:48:21.670 --> 00:48:22.838
It's so cold.

00:48:22.921 --> 00:48:24.131
Seo Mi-rae!

00:48:25.132 --> 00:48:26.466
Let's share this one.

00:48:26.550 --> 00:48:27.467
Okay.

00:48:30.554 --> 00:48:31.722
Thanks.

00:48:44.276 --> 00:48:47.279
I'll get out first, then you,
and Kyeong-nam will get out last.

00:48:56.496 --> 00:48:57.831
Rest up, guys.

00:48:57.914 --> 00:48:59.791
-Thank you, sir.
-Sure. Have a good night.

00:49:06.423 --> 00:49:07.424
Weather update.

00:49:07.507 --> 00:49:11.720
Snowfall centered over the central region
has continued since this evening.

00:49:11.803 --> 00:49:14.931
It is falling at a rate
of about 1 cm per hour in Seoul,

00:49:15.015 --> 00:49:17.976
Northern Gyeonggi-do,
and Yeongseo, Gangwon-do.

00:49:18.060 --> 00:49:19.770
Around the city…

00:49:19.853 --> 00:49:21.855
Sir, you can drop me off here.

00:49:21.938 --> 00:49:22.773
Sure thing.

00:49:29.446 --> 00:49:32.449
I'll be going now. Happy holidays.

00:49:32.532 --> 00:49:33.617
Wait.

00:49:37.245 --> 00:49:38.914
Take this. It's snowing a lot.

00:49:40.373 --> 00:49:42.793
It's fine.
We're right in front of my place.

00:49:42.876 --> 00:49:44.711
Goodbye, then.

00:50:02.604 --> 00:50:03.688
Ms. Seo!

00:50:13.115 --> 00:50:14.324
Take this.

00:50:17.702 --> 00:50:18.537
But I…

00:50:19.704 --> 00:50:20.622
I said I was okay.

00:50:23.250 --> 00:50:25.043
You won't accept anything from me?

00:50:27.379 --> 00:50:28.213
What?

00:50:35.178 --> 00:50:36.429
Just use it.

00:50:44.855 --> 00:50:48.567
How are you going to get home?
You can't hail a cab right now.

00:50:51.153 --> 00:50:52.404
I'll manage.

00:50:53.238 --> 00:50:54.072
Hey.

00:50:54.906 --> 00:50:55.740
Mr. Park.

00:50:56.616 --> 00:51:00.579
Take this back.
I don't want to accept this.

00:51:03.665 --> 00:51:05.709
I just don't want you to get snowed on.

00:51:06.960 --> 00:51:08.962
Does a small favor really bother you?

00:51:12.674 --> 00:51:13.842
Did I ever

00:51:14.551 --> 00:51:16.219
ask you to like me?

00:51:21.516 --> 00:51:22.517
Don't you think

00:51:24.144 --> 00:51:25.854
you're being too inconsiderate?

00:51:28.565 --> 00:51:30.775
Do you only care about your own feelings?

00:51:33.361 --> 00:51:35.363
I mean, have you considered

00:51:36.615 --> 00:51:38.116
how I might feel about things?

00:51:41.161 --> 00:51:42.329
This is

00:51:43.163 --> 00:51:44.331
hard for me too.

00:51:45.749 --> 00:51:49.753
I hate myself for how much I sway
every time you stir my heart.

00:51:50.378 --> 00:51:51.796
This is difficult for me too.

00:51:53.924 --> 00:51:56.259
But so what if I get swayed?

00:51:57.802 --> 00:51:59.221
What are you suggesting?

00:52:01.097 --> 00:52:02.599
That we start dating right away?

00:52:05.518 --> 00:52:06.811
Why can't we?

00:52:10.315 --> 00:52:11.650
Are you being serious?

00:52:11.733 --> 00:52:13.777
What are you so afraid of?

00:52:15.153 --> 00:52:17.239
We haven't even begun yet.

00:52:17.322 --> 00:52:18.990
If there's a beginning…

00:52:21.117 --> 00:52:22.744
there will be an end too.

00:52:22.827 --> 00:52:23.995
I…

00:52:26.414 --> 00:52:28.250
don't think about the end right now.

00:52:31.169 --> 00:52:34.673
For now, sure,
but you'll change eventually.

00:52:34.756 --> 00:52:36.591
Do you hate change that much?

00:52:37.717 --> 00:52:40.553
Is change really that bad?

00:52:43.431 --> 00:52:44.516
Ever since…

00:52:47.352 --> 00:52:49.020
I fell for you, Seo Mi-rae…

00:52:51.398 --> 00:52:52.565
I've changed.

00:57:37.767 --> 00:57:42.772
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon